{
  "text": "Analyses of the arterial images were performed with methods described by Veller et al. [CITATION_1] and others [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The only exception to the methodology described by Veller et al. [CITATION_4] was that ImageJ software system (National Institute of Health; http://rsb.info.-nih.gov/ij/) was used in place of the CalComp digitizing system. All ultrasound measurements preceded exercise testing and were recorded in mm. Arterial IMT was defined as the distance from the edge of the lumen-intima interface to the edge of the mediaadventitia interface; and, TWT was defined as the distance between the deep lining of the intima (endothelium) and the superficial wall of the adventitia [CITATION_5] . Vessel LD was defined as the distance from one edge of the lumen-intima interface to the edge of the opposing lumen-intima interface; and, W: L was calculated by dividing TWT by LD [CITATION_6] .",
